      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SAO PAULO SIMBA (7) is making terrific progress this campaign and made it three wins in a row at this circuit when scoring by 9m a fortnight ago. Up in distance and draws wider but he is going well enough to overcome both of those challenges. SINALOA (5) did a good job to come from wide on the back row for fifth to flying mare Captains Mistress in the G1 Rising Sun in Brisbane last start. Led for a second-up win here prior. Race fit now and could threaten. PICCADILLY PETE NZ (2) came from a wider barrier for third at Listed level last week. Placed the only time he attempted this longer distance and should get every chance from a low draw. PERFECT STRIDE NZ (8) rises in grade and draws wider but is back in winning form as is SOUTH SEAS ROCK NZ (6) who could be worth a spot in the exotics.",
